{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871625157,"sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a327adb001vLmTX6qlT8EPXp","messageID":"msg_d7a325d1f001lOWh48cVQ4IBhS","sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n16: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n17: │              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n18: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n19: │              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Key Interfaces\n24: \n25: #### CommandExecutor\n26: \n27: The primary interface for executing commands through PicoD.\n28: \n29: ```go\n30: type CommandExecutor interface {\n31:     Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n32:     ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n33:     GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n34:     Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n35:     StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n36: }\n37: ```\n38: \n39: #### ExecutionRequest\n40: \n41: Configuration for a command execution.\n42: \n43: ```go\n44: type ExecutionRequest struct {\n45:     Command     string\n46:     Args        []string\n47:     WorkingDir  string\n48:     Environment map[string]string\n49:     Timeout     time.Duration\n50:     ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints\n51:     SessionID   string\n52: }\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### ExecutionResult\n56: \n57: Result of a command execution.\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: type ExecutionResult struct {\n61:     ID         ExecutionID\n62:     Status     ExecutionStatus\n63:     ExitCode   int\n64:     Stdout     []byte\n65:     Stderr     []byte\n66:     StartedAt  time.Time\n67:     FinishedAt time.Time\n68:     Error      *ExecutionError\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ## Data Flow\n73: \n74: ### Synchronous Execution\n75: \n76: ```\n77: 1. Client calls Execute()\n78: 2. PicoD validates request and resource limits\n79: 3. Sandbox environment is prepared\n80: 4. Command is executed with monitoring\n81: 5. Output is captured\n82: 6. Result is returned to client\n83: ```\n84: \n85: ### Asynchronous Execution\n86: \n87: ```\n88: 1. Client calls ExecuteAsync()\n89: 2. Execution is queued with initial status \"pending\"\n90: 3. Background worker picks up execution\n91: 4. Status updates to \"running\"\n92: 5. Output is streamed to buffer\n93: 6. On completion, status updates to \"completed\" or \"failed\"\n94: 7. Client polls GetStatus() or receives callback\n95: ```\n96: \n97: ## Error Handling\n98: \n99: ### Error Types\n100: \n101: - `ErrInvalidRequest`: Malformed execution request\n102: - `ErrResourceExceeded`: Resource limits exceeded\n103: - `ErrTimeout`: Execution exceeded timeout\n104: - `ErrSandboxUnavailable`: Sandbox environment not available\n105: - `ErrExecutionFailed`: Command returned non-zero exit code\n106: - `ErrCancelled`: Execution was cancelled\n107: \n108: ### Status States\n109: \n110: ```\n111: pending → running → completed\n112:               ↓\n113:             failed\n114:               ↓\n115:            cancelled\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ## Security Considerations\n119: \n120: - Commands run in isolated sandbox environment\n121: - Resource limits enforced at sandbox level\n122: - No direct shell access\n123: - Environment variable filtering\n124: - Working directory restrictions\n125: \n126: ## Performance Considerations\n127: \n128: - Connection pooling to sandbox service\n129: - Output buffering with size limits\n130: - Concurrent execution limits\n131: - Timeout enforcement at multiple levels\n132: \n133: ## Open Questions\n134: \n135: 1. Maximum output size limits?\n136: 2. Real-time streaming protocol?\n137: 3. Multi-tenancy isolation model?\n138: 4. Execution queue prioritization?\n\n(End of file - total 138 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the PicoD command execution API for the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CommandExecutor  │  ExecutionManager  │  OutputBuffer  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│              Resource Limiter (Integration)              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/design.md","time":{"start":1775871625128,"end":1775871625155}}}}
