{"type":"text","timestamp":1775871660139,"sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a330d2d001eC82d4J0RZDKVx","messageID":"msg_d7a32ecaf0015Usk3BeeDNbYrd","sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the context needed. Let me write the comprehensive design.md document for AR-015 based on the specifications and existing project patterns:","time":{"start":1775871660138,"end":1775871660138}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775872007787,"sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a34044d001FBy6RSE2a4t0xe","messageID":"msg_d7a32ecaf0015Usk3BeeDNbYrd","sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","type":"text","text":"\\\"","time":{"start":1775872007780,"end":1775872007780}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775872008520,"sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a33106c0017hHYsP4uO9v4Zt","messageID":"msg_d7a32ecaf0015Usk3BeeDNbYrd","sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","content":"# AR-015 Design: PicoD Command Execution API\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-015  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe PicoD Command Execution API provides a unified interface for executing commands within sandboxed environments in the agentcube platform. It supports both synchronous and asynchronous execution modes, resource constraint enforcement, output capture and streaming, and complete execution lifecycle management.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Sandbox Interface (AR-009)**: For actual command execution in sandbox environments\n- **Status Store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)**: For execution status persistence\n- **client-go Library**: For Kubernetes API interactions with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Client Applications                                  │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\n│  │  Workload   │  │   CLI       │  │  Session    │                         │\n│  │  Manager    │  │   Toolkit   │  │  Manager    │                         │\n│  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\n└─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n          │                │                │\n          ▼                ▼                ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD CommandExecutor API                                 │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │                    CommandExecutor Interface                            │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n│  │  │   Execute()     │  │  ExecuteAsync() │  │   GetStatus()          │ │ │\n│  │  │   · Synchronous │  │  · Queue exec   │  │   · Query status       │ │ │\n│  │  │   · Blocking    │  │  · Return ID    │  │   · State transitions  │ │ │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐                             │ │\n│  │  │   Cancel()      │  │  StreamOutput() │                             │ │\n│  │  │   · Signal stop │  │  · Real-time    │                             │ │\n│  │  │   · Update state│  │  · Channel      │                             │ │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘                             │ │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                    Execution Management Layer                                │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  ExecutionQueue  │  │  StatusManager   │  │  OutputBuffer            │  │\n│  │  · FIFO queue    │  │  · State machine │  │  · Circular buffer       │  │\n│  │  · Priority      │  │  · Persistence   │  │  · Size limits           │  │\n│  │  · Concurrency   │  │  · Transitions   │  │  · Streaming             │  │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                    Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                                │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │  Sandbox Resolver│  │  Command Runner  │  │  Resource Limiter        │  │\n│  │  · Session lookup│  │  · Execute cmd   │  │  · Memory limits         │  │\n│  │  · Connection    │  │  · Stream I/O    │  │  · CPU throttling        │  │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                    Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                               │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                                │\n│  │  Redis/Valkey    │  │  ExecutionStore  │                                │\n│  │  · Status cache  │  │  · CRUD ops      │                                │\n│  │  · TTL support   │  │  · Query         │                                │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘                                │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Command Execution Flow                               │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Client  │──▶│  Execute │──▶│ Validate │──▶│ Generate │──▶│  Check   │  │\n│  │  Request │   │  Method  │   │  Request │   │    ID    │   │  Sandbox │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n│                                                                    │        │\n│                              ┌─────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n│                              ▼                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Return  │◀──│  Capture │◀──│  Execute │◀──│  Prepare │◀──│  Resolve │  │\n│  │  Result  │   │  Output  │   │  Command │   │  Sandbox │   │  Sandbox │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **CommandExecutor** | Primary API for command execution | `ExecutionRequest`, `ExecutionID` | `ExecutionResult`, `ExecutionStatus`, error |\n| **RequestValidator** | Validates execution requests | `ExecutionRequest` | Error or nil |\n| **ExecutionQueue** | Manages async execution queue | `ExecutionRequest` | `ExecutionID` |\n| **StatusManager** | Tracks and persists execution state | State transitions | Updated `ExecutionStatus` |\n| **OutputBuffer** | Captures and buffers command output | Output streams | `OutputChunk` channel |\n| **SandboxResolver** | Resolves session to sandbox | `SessionID` | `SandboxInfo` |\n| **ResourceLimiter** | Enforces resource constraints | `ResourceConstraints` | Enforced limits |\n| **ExecutionStore** | Persists execution metadata | `ExecutionStatus` | Stored status |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── executor.go              # CommandExecutor interface and implementation (~250 lines)\n├── types.go                 # ExecutionRequest, ExecutionResult, ExecutionStatus (~100 lines)\n├── status.go                # Status management and state transitions (~80 lines)\n├── output.go                # Output capture and streaming (~120 lines)\n├── errors.go                # Error type definitions (~50 lines)\n├── validation.go            # Request validation logic (~80 lines)\n├── config.go                # Configuration and defaults (~60 lines)\n└── executor_test.go         # Unit tests (~200 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Request DTOs\n\n#### ExecutionRequest\n\n```go\n// ExecutionRequest contains parameters for command execution.\ntype ExecutionRequest struct {\n    // Command is the command to execute (required)\n    Command string `json:\"command\" validate:\"required\"`\n\n    // Args are the command arguments\n    Args []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n\n    // WorkingDir is the working directory for execution (default: sandbox default)\n    WorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Environment defines environment variables (merged with sandbox defaults)\n    Environment map[string]string `json:\"environment,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Timeout is the maximum execution time (default: 30s)\n    Timeout time.Duration `json:\"timeout,omitempty\"`\n\n    // ResourceLimits defines resource constraints for execution\n    ResourceLimits ResourceConstraints `json:\"resourceLimits,omitempty\"`\n\n    // SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n    SessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n}\n\n// Validate validates the execution request.\nfunc (r *ExecutionRequest) Validate() error {\n    if strings.TrimSpace(r.Command) == \"\" {\n        return ErrInvalidCommand\n    }\n    if strings.Contains(r.Command, \"..\") || strings.Contains(r.Command, \"//\") {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: command contains invalid characters\", ErrInvalidCommand)\n    }\n    if r.SessionID == \"\" {\n        return ErrInvalidSessionID\n    }\n    if r.WorkingDir != \"\" && !isAllowedWorkingDir(r.WorkingDir) {\n        return ErrInvalidWorkingDir\n    }\n    for name := range r.Environment {\n        if !isValidEnvVarName(name) {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: invalid environment variable name: %s\", ErrInvalidRequest, name)\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Response DTOs\n\n#### ExecutionResult\n\n```go\n// ExecutionResult contains the result of a command execution.\ntype ExecutionResult struct {\n    // ID is the unique execution identifier\n    ID ExecutionID `json:\"id\"`\n\n    // Status contains the execution status details\n    Status ExecutionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n\n    // ExitCode is the command exit code (0 for success)\n    ExitCode int `json:\"exitCode\"`\n\n    // Stdout contains the captured standard output\n    Stdout []byte `json:\"stdout,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Stderr contains the captured standard error\n    Stderr []byte `json:\"stderr,omitempty\"`\n\n    // StartedAt is when execution started\n    StartedAt time.Time `json:\"startedAt\"`\n\n    // FinishedAt is when execution completed\n    FinishedAt time.Time `json:\"finishedAt\"`\n\n    // Error contains error details if execution failed\n    Error *ExecutionError `json:\"error,omitempty\"`\n\n    // Truncated indicates if output was truncated due to size limits\n    Truncated bool `json:\"truncated,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// ExecutionError contains detailed error information.\ntype ExecutionError struct {\n    // Code is the machine-readable error code\n    Code string `json:\"code\"`\n\n    // Message is the human-readable error message\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n\n    // Details contains additional error context\n    Details map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionStatus\n\n```go\n// ExecutionStatus represents the current state of an execution.\ntype ExecutionStatus struct {\n    // ID is the unique execution identifier\n    ID ExecutionID `json:\"id\"`\n\n    // State is the current execution state\n    State ExecutionState `json:\"state\"`\n\n    // StartedAt is when execution started (nil if not started)\n    StartedAt *time.Time `json:\"startedAt,omitempty\"`\n\n    // FinishedAt is when execution completed (nil if not finished)\n    FinishedAt *time.Time `json:\"finishedAt,omitempty\"`\n\n    // ExitCode is the command exit code (nil if not finished)\n    ExitCode *int `json:\"exitCode,omitempty\"`\n\n    // OutputRef references stored output (for large outputs)\n    OutputRef string `json:\"outputRef,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// ExecutionState represents the state of command execution.\ntype ExecutionState string\n\nconst (\n    // StatePending indicates the execution is queued\n    StatePending ExecutionState = \"pending\"\n\n    // StateRunning indicates the execution is in progress\n    StateRunning ExecutionState = \"running\"\n\n    // StateCompleted indicates the execution completed successfully\n    StateCompleted ExecutionState = \"completed\"\n\n    // StateFailed indicates the execution failed\n    StateFailed ExecutionState = \"failed\"\n\n    // StateCancelled indicates the execution was cancelled\n    StateCancelled ExecutionState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n\n// IsTerminal returns true if the state is terminal (completed, failed, or cancelled).\nfunc (s ExecutionState) IsTerminal() bool {\n    return s == StateCompleted || s == StateFailed || s == StateCancelled\n}\n```\n\n### Domain Types\n\n#### ResourceConstraints\n\n```go\n// ResourceConstraints defines resource limits for execution.\ntype ResourceConstraints struct {\n    // MaxMemory is the maximum memory in bytes (0 = unlimited)\n    MaxMemory int64 `json:\"maxMemory,omitempty\"`\n\n    // MaxCPU is the maximum CPU percentage (0-100, 0 = unlimited)\n    MaxCPU float64 `json:\"maxCpu,omitempty\"`\n\n    // MaxIOBytes is the maximum IO bandwidth in bytes per second (0 = unlimited)\n    MaxIOBytes int64 `json:\"maxIoBytes,omitempty\"`\n\n    // MaxFiles is the maximum number of open file descriptors (0 = unlimited)\n    MaxFiles int `json:\"maxFiles,omitempty\"`\n}\n\n// IsEmpty returns true if no constraints are set.\nfunc (r ResourceConstraints) IsEmpty() bool {\n    return r.MaxMemory == 0 && r.MaxCPU == 0 && r.MaxIOBytes == 0 && r.MaxFiles == 0\n}\n\n// Validate validates resource constraints.\nfunc (r ResourceConstraints) Validate() error {\n    if r.MaxMemory < 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxMemory cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n    }\n    if r.MaxCPU < 0 || r.MaxCPU > 100 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxCpu must be between 0 and 100\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n    }\n    if r.MaxIOBytes < 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxIoBytes cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n    }\n    if r.MaxFiles < 0 {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: maxFiles cannot be negative\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### OutputChunk\n\n```go\n// OutputChunk represents a piece of output from a command.\ntype OutputChunk struct {\n    // Data is the output data\n    Data []byte `json:\"data\"`\n\n    // Type indicates the output source\n    Type OutputType `json:\"type\"`\n\n    // Timestamp is when the output was captured\n    Timestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n}\n\n// OutputType indicates the source of output.\ntype OutputType string\n\nconst (\n    // Stdout indicates standard output\n    Stdout OutputType = \"stdout\"\n\n    // Stderr indicates standard error\n    Stderr OutputType = \"stderr\"\n)\n```\n\n### Internal Types\n\n#### CommandExecutor\n\n```go\n// ExecutionID uniquely identifies a command execution.\ntype ExecutionID string\n\n// CommandExecutor defines the interface for executing commands in sandboxes.\ntype CommandExecutor interface {\n    // Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n    // Blocks until execution completes, times out, or is cancelled.\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n\n    // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n    // Returns immediately; use GetStatus to poll for completion.\n    ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n\n    // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n    // Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if the execution does not exist.\n    GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n\n    // Cancel stops a running execution.\n    // Returns ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete if execution is in terminal state.\n    Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n\n    // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n    // Channel is closed when execution completes or context is cancelled.\n    StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n}\n\n// executor implements CommandExecutor.\ntype executor struct {\n    // store persists execution status\n    store ExecutionStore\n\n    // sandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox info\n    sandboxResolver SandboxResolver\n\n    // queue manages async execution queue\n    queue ExecutionQueue\n\n    // config contains executor configuration\n    config ExecutorConfig\n\n    // outputBuffers stores output buffers by execution ID\n    outputBuffers map[ExecutionID]*OutputBuffer\n\n    // mu protects outputBuffers\n    mu sync.RWMutex\n\n    // ctx is the executor context for background workers\n    ctx context.Context\n\n    // cancel cancels the executor context\n    cancel context.CancelFunc\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionStore\n\n```go\n// ExecutionStore defines the interface for execution status persistence.\ntype ExecutionStore interface {\n    // CreateStatus creates a new execution status record.\n    CreateStatus(ctx context.Context, status *ExecutionStatus) error\n\n    // GetStatus retrieves execution status by ID.\n    // Returns ErrExecutionNotFound if not found.\n    GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n\n    // UpdateStatus updates execution status.\n    UpdateStatus(ctx context.Context, status *ExecutionStatus) error\n\n    // UpdateStatusWithTransition updates status with state transition validation.\n    // Only allows valid state transitions.\n    UpdateStatusWithTransition(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID, from, to ExecutionState, updateFn func(*ExecutionStatus)) error\n\n    // DeleteStatus removes an execution status record.\n    DeleteStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n\n    // ListExecutions lists executions filtered by state and session.\n    ListExecutions(ctx context.Context, filter ExecutionFilter) ([]*ExecutionStatus, error)\n\n    // StoreOutput stores execution output for later retrieval.\n    StoreOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID, stdout, stderr []byte) error\n\n    // GetOutput retrieves stored execution output.\n    GetOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (stdout, stderr []byte, err error)\n}\n\n// ExecutionFilter defines filters for listing executions.\ntype ExecutionFilter struct {\n    // SessionID filters by session\n    SessionID string\n\n    // State filters by execution state\n    State ExecutionState\n\n    // Limit limits the number of results\n    Limit int\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutionQueue\n\n```go\n// ExecutionQueue manages the async execution queue.\ntype ExecutionQueue interface {\n    // Enqueue adds an execution request to the queue.\n    // Returns the assigned execution ID.\n    Enqueue(req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n\n    // Dequeue retrieves the next pending execution.\n    // Blocks until an execution is available or context is cancelled.\n    Dequeue(ctx context.Context) (*QueuedExecution, error)\n\n    // GetPosition returns the queue position for an execution.\n    GetPosition(id ExecutionID) (int, error)\n\n    // Remove removes an execution from the queue.\n    Remove(id ExecutionID) error\n\n    // Size returns the current queue size.\n    Size() int\n}\n\n// QueuedExecution represents an execution in the queue.\ntype QueuedExecution struct {\n    ID      ExecutionID\n    Request ExecutionRequest\n    EnqueuedAt time.Time\n}\n\n// executionQueue implements ExecutionQueue.\ntype executionQueue struct {\n    // items is the ordered queue of executions\n    items []*QueuedExecution\n\n    // mu protects items\n    mu sync.RWMutex\n\n    // cond signals when items are added\n    cond *sync.Cond\n\n    // idGen generates unique IDs\n    idGen func() ExecutionID\n}\n```\n\n#### OutputBuffer\n\n```go\n// OutputBuffer provides circular buffer for command output.\ntype OutputBuffer struct {\n    // id is the execution ID\n    id ExecutionID\n\n    // buffer is the circular buffer for output\n    buffer *ring.Ring\n\n    // mu protects buffer\n    mu sync.RWMutex\n\n    // subscribers are channels to broadcast output to\n    subscribers []chan OutputChunk\n\n    // subMu protects subscribers\n    subMu sync.RWMutex\n\n    // closed indicates if the buffer is closed\n    closed bool\n\n    // maxSize is the maximum buffer size\n    maxSize int\n}\n\n// NewOutputBuffer creates a new output buffer.\nfunc NewOutputBuffer(id ExecutionID, maxSize int) *OutputBuffer {\n    return &OutputBuffer{\n        id:      id,\n        buffer:  ring.New(maxSize),\n        maxSize: maxSize,\n    }\n}\n\n// Write writes output to the buffer.\nfunc (b *OutputBuffer) Write(data []byte, typ OutputType) {\n    b.mu.Lock()\n    defer b.mu.Unlock()\n\n    if b.closed {\n        return\n    }\n\n    chunk := OutputChunk{\n        Data:      data,\n        Type:      typ,\n        Timestamp: time.Now(),\n    }\n\n    b.buffer.Value = chunk\n    b.buffer = b.buffer.Next()\n\n    // Broadcast to subscribers\n    b.broadcast(chunk)\n}\n\n// Subscribe returns a channel for receiving output chunks.\nfunc (b *OutputBuffer) Subscribe() <-chan OutputChunk {\n    b.subMu.Lock()\n    defer b.subMu.Unlock()\n\n    ch := make(chan OutputChunk, 100)\n    b.subscribers = append(b.subscribers, ch)\n\n    // Send buffered output to new subscriber\n    b.mu.RLock()\n    b.buffer.Do(func(v interface{}) {\n        if v != nil {\n            select {\n            case ch <- v.(OutputChunk):\n            default:\n            }\n        }\n    })\n    b.mu.RUnlock()\n\n    return ch\n}\n\n// Close closes the buffer and all subscriber channels.\nfunc (b *OutputBuffer) Close() {\n    b.mu.Lock()\n    b.closed = true\n    b.mu.Unlock()\n\n    b.subMu.Lock()\n    for _, ch := range b.subscribers {\n        close(ch)\n    }\n    b.subscribers = nil\n    b.subMu.Unlock()\n}\n```\n\n#### ExecutorConfig\n\n```go\n// ExecutorConfig contains configuration for CommandExecutor.\ntype ExecutorConfig struct {\n    // DefaultTimeout is the default execution timeout\n    DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n\n    // MaxConcurrentExecutions limits concurrent executions\n    MaxConcurrentExecutions int\n\n    // MaxOutputSize is the maximum output capture size\n    MaxOutputSize int64\n\n    // OutputBufferSize is the output buffer size for streaming\n    OutputBufferSize int\n\n    // MaxExecutionQueueSize limits the async queue size\n    MaxExecutionQueueSize int\n\n    // ExecutionTTL is how long to retain execution records\n    ExecutionTTL time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultConfig returns the default executor configuration.\nfunc DefaultConfig() ExecutorConfig {\n    return ExecutorConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout:          30 * time.Second,\n        MaxConcurrentExecutions: 100,\n        MaxOutputSize:           10 * 1024 * 1024, // 10MB\n        OutputBufferSize:        4 * 1024,          // 4KB\n        MaxExecutionQueueSize:   1000,\n        ExecutionTTL:            24 * time.Hour,\n    }\n}\n\n// ConfigFromEnv loads configuration from environment variables.\nfunc ConfigFromEnv() ExecutorConfig {\n    cfg := DefaultConfig()\n\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_DEFAULT_TIMEOUT\"); v != \"\" {\n        if d, err := time.ParseDuration(v); err == nil {\n            cfg.DefaultTimeout = d\n        }\n    }\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_CONCURRENT\"); v != \"\" {\n        if n, err := strconv.Atoi(v); err == nil {\n            cfg.MaxConcurrentExecutions = n\n        }\n    }\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_OUTPUT_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if n, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 64); err == nil {\n            cfg.MaxOutputSize = n\n        }\n    }\n    if v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_OUTPUT_BUFFER_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n        if n, err := strconv.Atoi(v); err == nil {\n            cfg.OutputBufferSize = n\n        }\n    }\n\n    return cfg\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\n// Default configuration values\nconst (\n    // DefaultTimeout is the default execution timeout (30 seconds)\n    DefaultTimeout = 30 * time.Second\n\n    // DefaultMaxConcurrent is the default concurrent execution limit\n    DefaultMaxConcurrent = 100\n\n    // DefaultMaxOutputSize is the default max output size (10MB)\n    DefaultMaxOutputSize = 10 * 1024 * 1024\n\n    // DefaultOutputBufferSize is the default output buffer size (4KB)\n    DefaultOutputBufferSize = 4 * 1024\n\n    // ExecutionIDLength is the length of generated execution IDs\n    ExecutionIDLength = 16\n\n    // ExecutionIDPrefix is the prefix for execution IDs\n    ExecutionIDPrefix = \"exec-\"\n)\n\n// Error codes\nconst (\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidRequest indicates malformed request\n    ErrorCodeInvalidRequest = \"INVALID_REQUEST\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidCommand indicates empty or invalid command\n    ErrorCodeInvalidCommand = \"INVALID_COMMAND\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID indicates missing or invalid session ID\n    ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID = \"INVALID_SESSION_ID\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidWorkingDir indicates invalid working directory\n    ErrorCodeInvalidWorkingDir = \"INVALID_WORKING_DIR\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeResourceExceeded indicates resource limits exceeded\n    ErrorCodeResourceExceeded = \"RESOURCE_EXCEEDED\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeTimeout indicates execution timeout\n    ErrorCodeTimeout = \"TIMEOUT\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable indicates sandbox not accessible\n    ErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable = \"SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeExecutionFailed indicates command returned non-zero exit\n    ErrorCodeExecutionFailed = \"EXECUTION_FAILED\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeExecutionNotFound indicates execution ID not found\n    ErrorCodeExecutionNotFound = \"EXECUTION_NOT_FOUND\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeExecutionAlreadyComplete indicates cannot cancel completed execution\n    ErrorCodeExecutionAlreadyComplete = \"EXECUTION_ALREADY_COMPLETE\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeTooManyConcurrent indicates concurrent limit exceeded\n    ErrorCodeTooManyConcurrent = \"TOO_MANY_CONCURRENT\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeCancelled indicates execution was cancelled\n    ErrorCodeCancelled = \"CANCELLED\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### CommandExecutor Interface\n\n```go\n// CommandExecutor is the primary API for PicoD command execution.\ntype CommandExecutor interface {\n    // Execute runs a command synchronously and returns the result.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n    //   - req: Execution request containing command, args, and options\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - *ExecutionResult: Result containing exit code, output, and timing\n    //   - error: ErrInvalidRequest, ErrTimeout, ErrSandboxUnavailable, etc.\n    Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n\n    // ExecuteAsync runs a command asynchronously and returns an execution ID.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - ctx: Context for the enqueue operation\n    //   - req: Execution request\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - ExecutionID: Unique identifier for tracking the execution\n    //   - error: ErrInvalidRequest, ErrTooManyConcurrent, etc.\n    ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error)\n\n    // GetStatus retrieves the current status of an execution.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - ctx: Context for the operation\n    //   - id: Execution identifier\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - *ExecutionStatus: Current execution status\n    //   - error: ErrExecutionNotFound\n    GetStatus(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (*ExecutionStatus, error)\n\n    // Cancel stops a running execution.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - ctx: Context for the operation\n    //   - id: Execution identifier\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - error: nil on success, ErrExecutionNotFound, ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete\n    Cancel(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) error\n\n    // StreamOutput returns a channel for streaming output from an execution.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - ctx: Context for the streaming operation\n    //   - id: Execution identifier\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - <-chan OutputChunk: Channel receiving output chunks\n    //   - error: ErrExecutionNotFound\n    StreamOutput(ctx context.Context, id ExecutionID) (<-chan OutputChunk, error)\n}\n```\n\n### Execution State Transitions\n\n```\n                    ┌─────────────┐\n         ┌─────────▶│   Pending   │◀────────┐\n         │          │  (queued)   │         │\n         │          └──────┬──────┘         │\n         │                 │ dequeue        │ enqueue\n         │                 ▼                │\n         │          ┌─────────────┐         │\n         │          │   Running   │─────────┤\n         │          │ (executing) │         │\n         │          └──────┬──────┘         │\n         │                 │                │\n    cancel│         ┌──────┼──────┐         │\n         │         ▼      ▼      ▼         │\n         │    ┌────────┐ ┌────────┐ ┌──────────┐\n         └───▶│Failed  │ │Completed│ │Cancelled │\n              │(error) │ │(success)│ │(stopped) │\n              └────────┘ └────────┘ └──────────┘\n```\n\n**Valid Transitions:**\n- `pending` → `running` (when dequeued and started)\n- `pending` → `cancelled` (if cancelled before start)\n- `running` → `completed` (on successful exit)\n- `running` → `failed` (on non-zero exit or error)\n- `running` → `cancelled` (on cancellation)\n\n### Service Interface\n\n```go\n// SandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox information.\ntype SandboxResolver interface {\n    // Resolve returns sandbox info for a session ID.\n    // Returns ErrSandboxNotFound if session doesn't exist.\n    Resolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\n// SandboxRunner executes commands in a sandbox.\ntype SandboxRunner interface {\n    // Run executes a command synchronously.\n    Run(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error)\n\n    // Start begins async command execution.\n    Start(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, req ExecutionRequest) error\n\n    // Cancel stops a running command.\n    Cancel(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, id ExecutionID) error\n}\n\n// PicoDService provides high-level PicoD operations.\ntype PicoDService interface {\n    // CommandExecutor returns the command executor.\n    CommandExecutor() CommandExecutor\n\n    // Health returns the service health status.\n    Health(ctx context.Context) error\n\n    // Shutdown gracefully shuts down the service.\n    Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories and Codes\n\n| Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n|-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed execution request | No | Return with field details |\n| `ErrInvalidCommand` | `INVALID_COMMAND` | Empty or invalid command | No | Return with command details |\n| `ErrInvalidSessionID` | `INVALID_SESSION_ID` | Missing session ID | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrInvalidWorkingDir` | `INVALID_WORKING_DIR` | Invalid working directory | No | Return 400 |\n| `ErrResourceExceeded` | `RESOURCE_EXCEEDED` | Resource limits exceeded | Yes | Retry with lower limits |\n| `ErrTimeout` | `TIMEOUT` | Execution exceeded timeout | Yes | Retry with longer timeout |\n| `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox not accessible | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n| `ErrExecutionFailed` | `EXECUTION_FAILED` | Command returned non-zero | No | Return with exit code |\n| `ErrExecutionNotFound` | `EXECUTION_NOT_FOUND` | Execution ID not found | No | Return 404 |\n| `ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete` | `EXECUTION_ALREADY_COMPLETE` | Cannot cancel completed | No | Return 409 |\n| `ErrTooManyConcurrent` | `TOO_MANY_CONCURRENT` | Concurrent limit exceeded | Yes | Queue or return 429 |\n| `ErrCancelled` | `CANCELLED` | Execution was cancelled | No | Return cancellation status |\n\n### Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\n// PicoD execution errors\nvar (\n    ErrInvalidRequest              = errors.New(\"picod: invalid request\")\n    ErrInvalidCommand              = errors.New(\"picod: command is required\")\n    ErrInvalidSessionID            = errors.New(\"picod: session ID is required\")\n    ErrInvalidWorkingDir           = errors.New(\"picod: invalid working directory\")\n    ErrResourceExceeded            = errors.New(\"picod: resource limits exceeded\")\n    ErrTimeout                     = errors.New(\"picod: execution timeout\")\n    ErrSandboxUnavailable          = errors.New(\"picod: sandbox unavailable\")\n    ErrExecutionFailed             = errors.New(\"picod: execution failed\")\n    ErrExecutionNotFound           = errors.New(\"picod: execution not found\")\n    ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete    = errors.New(\"picod: execution already complete\")\n    ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions = errors.New(\"picod: too many concurrent executions\")\n    ErrCancelled                   = errors.New(\"picod: execution cancelled\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Executor-Level Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (e *executor) Execute(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (*ExecutionResult, error) {\n    // Validate request\n    if err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidRequest, err)\n    }\n\n    // Apply default timeout\n    if req.Timeout == 0 {\n        req.Timeout = e.config.DefaultTimeout\n    }\n\n    // Check concurrent limit\n    if !e.acquireExecutionSlot(ctx) {\n        return nil, ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions\n    }\n    defer e.releaseExecutionSlot()\n\n    // Resolve sandbox\n    sandbox, err := e.sandboxResolver.Resolve(ctx, req.SessionID)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n    }\n\n    // Execute with timeout context\n    execCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, req.Timeout)\n    defer cancel()\n\n    result, err := e.runCommand(execCtx, sandbox, req)\n    if err != nil {\n        if errors.Is(err, context.DeadlineExceeded) {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: execution exceeded %v\", ErrTimeout, req.Timeout)\n        }\n        if errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: execution was cancelled\", ErrCancelled)\n        }\n        return nil, err\n    }\n\n    return result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### State Transition Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (s *executionStore) UpdateStatusWithTransition(\n    ctx context.Context,\n    id ExecutionID,\n    from, to ExecutionState,\n    updateFn func(*ExecutionStatus),\n) error {\n    // Validate state transition\n    if !isValidTransition(from, to) {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"invalid state transition from %s to %s\", from, to)\n    }\n\n    // Get current status\n    status, err := s.GetStatus(ctx, id)\n    if err != nil {\n        return err\n    }\n\n    // Check current state matches expected\n    if status.State != from {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"execution %s is in state %s, expected %s\", id, status.State, from)\n    }\n\n    // Check if already in terminal state\n    if status.State.IsTerminal() {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: execution is in terminal state %s\", ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete, status.State)\n    }\n\n    // Apply update\n    status.State = to\n    if updateFn != nil {\n        updateFn(status)\n    }\n\n    // Persist\n    return s.UpdateStatus(ctx, status)\n}\n\nfunc isValidTransition(from, to ExecutionState) bool {\n    transitions := map[ExecutionState][]ExecutionState{\n        StatePending:   {StateRunning, StateCancelled},\n        StateRunning:   {StateCompleted, StateFailed, StateCancelled},\n        StateCompleted: {},\n        StateFailed:    {},\n        StateCancelled: {},\n    }\n    valid, ok := transitions[from]\n    if !ok {\n        return false\n    }\n    for _, s := range valid {\n        if s == to {\n            return true\n        }\n    }\n    return false\n}\n```\n\n#### Concurrent Execution Management\n\n```go\nfunc (e *executor) acquireExecutionSlot(ctx context.Context) bool {\n    select {\n    case e.executionSem <- struct{}{}:\n        return true\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        return false\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (e *executor) releaseExecutionSlot() {\n    select {\n    case <-e.executionSem:\n    default:\n    }\n}\n\nfunc (e *executor) ExecuteAsync(ctx context.Context, req ExecutionRequest) (ExecutionID, error) {\n    if err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n        return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidRequest, err)\n    }\n\n    // Check queue capacity\n    if e.queue.Size() >= e.config.MaxExecutionQueueSize {\n        return \"\", ErrTooManyConcurrentExecutions\n    }\n\n    // Enqueue\n    id, err := e.queue.Enqueue(req)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n\n    // Create initial status\n    status := &ExecutionStatus{\n        ID:    id,\n        State: StatePending,\n    }\n    if err := e.store.CreateStatus(ctx, status); err != nil {\n        e.queue.Remove(id)\n        return \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create status: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    return id, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Error Wrapping and Propagation\n\n```go\n// Error wrapping pattern with context\nif err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to resolve sandbox for session %s: %w\", req.SessionID, err)\n}\n\n// Error checking with context\nif errors.Is(err, ErrSandboxUnavailable) {\n    // Retry with backoff\n}\n\n// Kubernetes API error mapping\nfunc mapSandboxError(err error) error {\n    if errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound) {\n        return ErrSandboxUnavailable\n    }\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestExecutor_Execute_Success(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup mocks\n    mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n    mockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n    mockRunner := new(mockSandboxRunner)\n\n    executor := NewExecutor(ExecutorConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n    }, mockStore, mockResolver, mockRunner)\n\n    // Setup expectations\n    sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n        SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n        PodIP:     \"10.0.0.1\",\n    }\n    mockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n    mockRunner.On(\"Run\", mock.Anything, sandbox, mock.Anything).Return(&ExecutionResult{\n        ExitCode: 0,\n        Stdout:   []byte(\"hello\\n\"),\n    }, nil)\n\n    // Execute\n    result, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n        Command:   \"echo\",\n        Args:      []string{\"hello\"},\n        SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n    })\n\n    // Assert\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, 0, result.ExitCode)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"hello\\n\", string(result.Stdout))\n    mockResolver.AssertExpectations(t)\n    mockRunner.AssertExpectations(t)\n}\n\nfunc TestExecutor_Execute_InvalidCommand(t *testing.T) {\n    executor := NewExecutor(DefaultConfig(), nil, nil, nil)\n\n    _, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n        Command:   \"\",\n        SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n    })\n\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrInvalidCommand)\n}\n\nfunc TestExecutor_Execute_Timeout(t *testing.T) {\n    mockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n    mockRunner := new(mockSandboxRunner)\n\n    executor := NewExecutor(ExecutorConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout: 100 * time.Millisecond,\n    }, nil, mockResolver, mockRunner)\n\n    sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n    mockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n    mockRunner.On(\"Run\", mock.Anything, sandbox, mock.Anything).Run(func(args mock.Arguments) {\n        ctx := args.Get(0).(context.Context)\n        <-ctx.Done() // Block until cancelled\n    }).Return(nil, context.DeadlineExceeded)\n\n    _, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n        Command:   \"sleep\",\n        Args:      []string{\"10\"},\n        SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n    })\n\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrTimeout)\n}\n\nfunc TestExecutor_ExecuteAsync(t *testing.T) {\n    mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n    mockQueue := new(mockExecutionQueue)\n\n    executor := &executor{\n        store: mockStore,\n        queue: mockQueue,\n        config: ExecutorConfig{\n            MaxExecutionQueueSize: 100,\n        },\n    }\n\n    mockQueue.On(\"Size\").Return(0)\n    mockQueue.On(\"Enqueue\", mock.Anything).Return(ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), nil)\n    mockStore.On(\"CreateStatus\", mock.Anything, mock.Anything).Return(nil)\n\n    id, err := executor.ExecuteAsync(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n        Command:   \"long-running-task\",\n        SessionID: \"sess-123\",\n    })\n\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), id)\n    mockQueue.AssertExpectations(t)\n    mockStore.AssertExpectations(t)\n}\n\nfunc TestExecutor_GetStatus(t *testing.T) {\n    mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n    executor := &executor{store: mockStore}\n\n    expectedStatus := &ExecutionStatus{\n        ID:    ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"),\n        State: StateRunning,\n    }\n    mockStore.On(\"GetStatus\", mock.Anything, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")).Return(expectedStatus, nil)\n\n    status, err := executor.GetStatus(context.Background(), ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"))\n\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, StateRunning, status.State)\n}\n\nfunc TestExecutor_Cancel(t *testing.T) {\n    mockStore := new(mockExecutionStore)\n    mockRunner := new(mockSandboxRunner)\n    mockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n\n    executor := &executor{\n        store:           mockStore,\n        sandboxRunner:   mockRunner,\n        sandboxResolver: mockResolver,\n    }\n\n    status := &ExecutionStatus{\n        ID:    ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"),\n        State: StateRunning,\n    }\n    sandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{SessionID: \"sess-123\"}\n\n    mockStore.On(\"GetStatus\", mock.Anything, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")).Return(status, nil)\n    mockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n    mockRunner.On(\"Cancel\", mock.Anything, sandbox, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")).Return(nil)\n    mockStore.On(\"UpdateStatusWithTransition\", mock.Anything, ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), StateRunning, StateCancelled, mock.Anything).Return(nil)\n\n    err := executor.Cancel(context.Background(), ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"))\n\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n}\n\nfunc TestExecutor_StreamOutput(t *testing.T) {\n    executor := &executor{\n        outputBuffers: make(map[ExecutionID]*OutputBuffer),\n    }\n\n    // Create buffer with some output\n    buf := NewOutputBuffer(ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"), 100)\n    buf.Write([]byte(\"line1\\n\"), Stdout)\n    buf.Write([]byte(\"line2\\n\"), Stdout)\n    executor.outputBuffers[ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\")] = buf\n\n    ch, err := executor.StreamOutput(context.Background(), ExecutionID(\"exec-abc123\"))\n\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Receive chunks\n    var chunks []OutputChunk\n    for chunk := range ch {\n        chunks = append(chunks, chunk)\n    }\n\n    assert.Len(t, chunks, 2)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"line1\\n\", string(chunks[0].Data))\n    assert.Equal(t, \"line2\\n\", string(chunks[1].Data))\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestIntegration_ExecuteWithRealStore(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n    }\n\n    // Setup real Redis store\n    store := setupTestRedis(t)\n    defer store.Close()\n\n    executor := NewExecutor(DefaultConfig(), store, mockResolver, mockRunner)\n\n    // Test full execution flow\n    result, err := executor.Execute(context.Background(), ExecutionRequest{\n        Command:   \"echo\",\n        Args:      []string{\"integration test\"},\n        SessionID: \"test-session\",\n    })\n\n    assert.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, 0, result.ExitCode)\n}\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Test Case | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------|-----------------|\n| Sync execution success | `TestExecute_Success` | Returns result with exit code 0 |\n| Sync execution failure | `TestExecute_CommandFailure` | Returns result with non-zero exit code |\n| Sync execution timeout | `TestExecute_Timeout` | Returns ErrTimeout |\n| Invalid command | `TestExecute_InvalidCommand` | Returns ErrInvalidCommand |\n| Invalid session | `TestExecute_InvalidSession` | Returns ErrInvalidSessionID |\n| Async execution | `TestExecuteAsync` | Returns execution ID |\n| Queue full | `TestExecuteAsync_QueueFull` | Returns ErrTooManyConcurrent |\n| Get status | `TestGetStatus` | Returns correct status |\n| Status not found | `TestGetStatus_NotFound` | Returns ErrExecutionNotFound |\n| Cancel running | `TestCancel` | Updates status to cancelled |\n| Cancel completed | `TestCancel_AlreadyComplete` | Returns ErrExecutionAlreadyComplete |\n| Stream output | `TestStreamOutput` | Receives all output chunks |\n| Context cancellation | `TestExecute_ContextCancel` | Returns ErrCancelled |\n| Resource limits | `TestExecute_ResourceLimits` | Enforces constraints |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | ExecutionID generation |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API client |\n\n### Internal Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | SandboxInfo shared types |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Execution store interface |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| WorkloadManager | Execute commands in sandboxes |\n| Session Manager | User session command execution |\n| CLI Toolkit | Synchronous command execution |\n| Idle Cleanup Worker | Query active executions |\n\n---\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Latency | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|---------|-------|\n| Execute (sync) | O(1) | Command-dependent | Blocking until completion |\n| ExecuteAsync | O(1) | < 10ms | Queue insertion |\n| GetStatus | O(1) | < 5ms | Store lookup |\n| Cancel | O(1) | < 10ms | Signal + status update |\n| StreamOutput | O(n) | Real-time | n = output chunks |\n| Resolve Sandbox | O(1) | < 5ms | Store or cache lookup |\n\n### Resource Limits\n\n| Resource | Default | Maximum | Configurable |\n|----------|---------|---------|--------------|\n| Concurrent executions | 100 | 1000 | Yes |\n| Execution queue size | 1000 | 10000 | Yes |\n| Max output size | 10MB | 100MB | Yes |\n| Output buffer size | 4KB | 1MB | Yes |\n| Execution TTL | 24h | 7d | Yes |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- **Command Validation**: Rejects commands with path traversal attempts (`..`, `//`)\n- **Working Directory Restrictions**: Validates working directories against allowed paths\n- **Environment Variable Filtering**: Validates env var names (alphanumeric + underscore)\n- **Resource Limits**: Enforces CPU, memory, IO, and file descriptor limits\n- **Sandbox Isolation**: All commands run in isolated sandbox environments\n- **No Shell Access**: Direct command execution without shell interpolation\n- **Output Size Limits**: Prevents memory exhaustion from large outputs\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [PicoD Proposal](proposal.md) — Feature proposal and requirements\n- [PicoD Delta Spec](changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n- [PicoD Tests](changes/AR-015/tests.md) — Test specifications\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n- [AR-009 Sandbox](sandbox-orchestration/design.md) — Sandbox orchestration system\n- [AR-012 Session Store](session-store/design.md) — Storage interface\n- [AR-006 Lifecycle](changes/AR-006/design.md) — Lifecycle management patterns\n\n---\n\n*AR-015 — Module: pkg/picod — Language: Go — Size: M*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-015/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/common/types/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/redis_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":38,"character":26},"end":{"line":38,"character":38}},"severity":3,"code":"unusedparams","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedparams#unusedparams"},"source":"unusedparams","message":"unused parameter: t"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/store/store.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types/request.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/types/response.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":24,"character":6},"end":{"line":24,"character":17}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"http