{"type":"text","timestamp":1775872052206,"sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","part":{"id":"prt_d7a38f03e001z468UskWM3Kx7N","messageID":"msg_d7a386180001wI0H8rMquJYDXv","sessionID":"ses_285cdee22ffegkKhKhFXhG8RWF","type":"text","text":"I've created a comprehensive `design.md` file for the AR-015 PicoD Command Execution API. The document includes:\n\n**Structure:**\n1. **Overview** - AR details, module info, and integration points\n2. **Architecture** - High-level design diagrams and component interactions\n3. **Directory Structure** - File organization under `pkg/picod/`\n4. **Data Structures** - Complete type definitions including:\n   - `ExecutionRequest` with validation\n   - `ExecutionResult` with captured output\n   - `ExecutionStatus` with state management\n   - `ResourceConstraints` for limits\n   - `OutputChunk` for streaming\n   - Internal types: `CommandExecutor`, `ExecutionStore`, `ExecutionQueue`, `OutputBuffer`\n5. **API Contracts** - Interface definitions, state transition diagrams, and service interfaces\n6. **Error Handling** - Error codes, sentinel errors, and handling patterns\n7. **Testing Strategy** - Unit tests, integration tests, and test scenarios table\n8. **Dependencies** - External (uuid, client-go) and internal dependencies\n9. **Performance Characteristics** - Complexity analysis and resource limits\n10. **Security Considerations** - Command validation, resource limits, sandbox isolation\n11. **References** - Links to related project documents\n\nThe design follows the patterns established in the existing `design.md` (AR-006) and incorporates all specifications from `delta-spec.md`, `spec.yaml`, and `proposal.md`.","time":{"start":1775872052204,"end":1775872052204}}}
